headline: Accenture and Infroneer Launch AI-Powered JV to Transform Japan's Infrastructure
summary: On Tuesday, infrastructure services company Infroneer Holdings and Accenture (NYSE:ACN) announced an agreement to establish a joint venture (JV), Infroneer Strategy & Innovation, to resolve key issues and promote innovation for the safe and efficient construction and operation of infrastructure in Japan. Infroneer HD owns 81% of the JV, and Accenture has 19%. The companies will establish the JV on April 1, 2025, with ~100 employees. Also Read: Applied Materials Navigates China Slowdown, Analysts

headline: Clarivate PLC (CLVT) Q4 Earnings and Revenues Top Estimates
summary: Clarivate (CLVT) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of 5% and 0.75%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2024. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?
